inn1.comm: 143.6 kph right away, and it takes off from short of a good length just outside off stump, he has a poke at it, and gets bat out of the way belatedly as it zips past him
ooh, almost had him there, very full on leg stump, he chose to go on the back foot, and had a swipe across the line, the leading edge fell short of mid off
146 kph ripping yorker, Tait is right on the money here, he is pegged on the back foot, somehow manages to survive, jabs it away off the inside edge to fine leg
a bit away from off stump this time, Davison came forward and went for a loose drive, the ball moved away a shade to beat him, Tait has overstepped to allow a free hit
139.5 kph bouncer, Davison cannot get it away, probably expecting the fuller one, tried to upper cut it but missed

Tait bowls a pacy full delivery on the pads, dropped by Michael Hussey at square leg as it is flicked emphatically off the toes, it was going quickly over him, he managed to get two hands to it but only parried it away to the boundary
goes for a cover drive from the crease, is miles away from the length ball that leaves him a shade
139.9 kph, shrt and bit of width, he latches on to it in an instant, and cuts it superbly between cover and point
143.2 kph short and again some width, this time there is more effort from Lee, and he gets much more bounce, no footwork from Hiral who tries to have a swing from the crease, and is beaten
144.5 kph, he is alternating between connecting and missing, this time he delays the shot, goes deep in the crease and cuts it past backward point for another boundary

Lee has had enough of being cut, gets him to ungainly fend a bouncer that takes off, three fielders hare after it as it goes high over the keeper's head, one of them is keeper, one is slip, one is fine leg who manages to pull it back in, and there is a fourth fielder waiting inside the ropes to throw the ball back, as the earlier three have crossed the ropes, phew
shot, this is some start from Canada, as fine a cover drive as any, gets front foot out and shows the full face of the bat to get it in the gap, that is enough on this outfield
punched in the air off the back foot, but again in the gap past extra cover, and Canada are fairly racing away here
goes for the yorker right away, dug out in to the off side for a single

my goodness, that is murdered, Shaun Tait bowls one at 148.5 kph, but Hiral seems to be enjoying this battle, stays on the crease and thumps it over extra cover, one leg in the air in cavalier fashion as he does that, and the connection is so neat it goes all the way
Tait sprays it down the leg side, trying to go for the bouncer in to the body
142.6 kph, Tait has lost his radar, another one goes marginally down the leg side with the angle, that is enough for him to concede the wide in this format
back of a length and bounces awkwardly, but he gets outside the line to work it away to fine leg
Davison tries to get in to the act now, goes for the pull off one leg to a bouncer that is miles outside off stump, and missed
bowls one wide outside off stump on a length, and he goes down on the knee to cut it away to third man
goes for the slash to a short and wide delivery, Tait is fortunate to get away with it as he misses, not much footwork did Hiral in
goes for a swipe at this back of a length ball outside off stump, and Lee gets the outside edge, but it falls way short of Haddin
creamed off the front foot with lovely timing, but drives this full ball straight to Watson at short extra cover
smashed again, this time he gets it in the gap as Lee continues to go full in search of movement that he is not finding currently, cover had no chance as it sped past him
targets the stumps with a full length again, Davison stands in the crease and lifts it high over midwicket

that will do for Lee, and that will be the end of John Davison for one final time, the slow bouncer from Brett, got Davison in an awkward position as he tried to go for the hook, the ball took the glove and lobbed away to Haddin who pouched it
149.2 kph, Lee is charged after the wicket, bowls this one outside off stump and gets it to seam away, Surkari leaves it alone

gets some shape off the seam in to the batsman from a length, he flicks it in the air to Hussey at square leg, who has a shy at the non-striker's stumps with the batsman already in the crease, and concedes an overthrow off the ricochet
goes full and wide outside off stump, Hiral is in a mood to belt everything, bends the knee and slashes it past backward point, no chance for third man at all
Johnson beats him with a length ball that goes across him close to off stump, he goes for the drive and ends up playing inside the line

another maximum, not where he intended it, but Canada will take it, Johnson continues to bowl it fuller and wider outside off stump, he had a big swing at it, and got it miles in the air, Lee at third man got into position, but it eluded him and went just over the ropes
bounces from short of a length but down the pads, off the hip to square leg
gets one bang on target finally, length ball homing in on middle and off, defended with bat and pad close together
143.7 kph bouncer on off stump, he keeps the bat down and gets head out of the way, Lee has something to say to him, but he walks away towards square leg
comes very slowly off the pitch, almost stopping on the batsman, he stabs it in the air in front of point
fired wide down the leg side from back of a length
another shortish one on the pads, fended away down towards square leg
gets the short delivery on target around off stump, he leaves it well alone, swaying out of harm's way
Lee continues to pound him with the bouncer, gets this one high enough for it to be called wide, Hiral got down underneath it
gets away with this short delivery, it bounces high outside off stump, he was almost expecting it, neatly weaved out of the line when he saw it coming
he finally decides to take on the Lee bouncer, and what a way to deal with it, not in a great position but hooks it away in the air, and over deep square leg, what a start this is from Canada
good delivery, that angle across the right hander close to off stump, good bounce too, he has a prod and is beaten
goes a touch wider outside off stump and he leaves it alone this time
rides the bounce on one that jags back in to the body, and gets it wide of midwicket
goes right back in the crease, and plays out a back of a length ball with an open face on the off side
stands in the crease and has a go at a fuller delivery that is angled across him, the thick outside edge flies to Lee at third man
floats it much fuller outside off stump this time, egging him to go for the drive, but he shoulders arms after getting forward
lumbers in and bowls a fuller one outside off stump, driven to mid off
a touch shorter and cutting back in, pushed away to short midwicket
gets some width outside off, but cannot make use of it, slaps this one into the ground and the ball rolls away to cover
the lesser pace of Watson is making the ball stop and come on slowly, another attempt at a drive it mistimed to mid off
and again, looks to have a swing at one outside off stump, gets an inside edge onto pad
driven crisply off the front foot this time and a single is taken wide of mid off
gets behind one that comes in with the angle to push out to point
slings it in full on the pads, he tickles it down to fine leg
gets it to jag back in from short if a length, he rides the bounce to keep it down
similar delivery again, this time he shuffles across to work it away towards midwicket
Hiral continues to swing merrily, and picks up boundaries all around, has a swing at one angled across him on a length, and the outside edge at Johnson's pace gives third man no  chance
he gets away again, Watson at slip it is, very tough chance as it was dying to his right, he put in the dive but it seemed to bounce inches short as Hiral had another go, moves to 49 now
Hiral has one more swipe from the crease to one outside off stump, this time he misses
makes good ground and gets down to the other end with a desperate dive, the throw missed, and Hiral lives on to raise his bat for his half-century, it was hit down to mid off
Surkari this time, looks to steer on that is very close to the body, and gets an edge that scoots wide of Haddin
off the pads from short of a good length on the leg side
chooses to leave a length delivery on ite line outside off stump, but it cuts back in a long way, not far from off stump that one
has him in trouble with this one that jags back in sharply and bounces more than the previous one, goes over the stumps as he pushes outside the line
goes for the yorker right away, gets it down the pads off a very full length, flicked in the air past  midwicket
147.1 kph and zooming on to the stumps from a length, he remains deep in the crease to push it away on the off side
wants to belt this one down the ground, but gets it off the bottom half of the bat down the track to Tait
slashes a widish one away off the back foot to third man
148.2 kph fired on the pads, he misses out on the flick, Tait thinks it is hitting leg, umpire Saheba thinks it is going down, which it is
goes deep in the crease to a yorker length ball and shows the full face of the bat to send it straight down the track, that was timed sweetly, Tait manages to get a foot on it
squeezes one out in front of point and sets off for the single, sent back by the non-striker
shuffles and plays a length ball back to the bowler from the crease

finally Hiral's adventurous innings is over, he went for the slash to a short and wide delivery, got on his toes to counter the bounce, but got it high in the air, and safely down to Mitch on the third man boundary who takes it cleanly, but what a knock from the kid
takes a step outside the crease and blocks one off the edge on to pad
takes two steps down the track this time, but can only manage to pat it away, smart work from Watson, keeping it tight
almost got him, he chopped this one off the back foot, and Haddin cannot get how it missed the stumps and rolled away fine
half-forward to a 146.9 kph length ball outside off stump, and half-drives it away towards extra cover
Tait looks for the lethal yorker at 148.4 kph, almost gets it right, he gets an inside edge on to boot that saves him
tries the short one that does not get up much outside off stump, he weaves out of the way nevertheless
147.6 kph fullish one, he goes back, perilous approach, but gets bat down in time to push it back to Tait, who threatens to throw the ball at the batsman
played out in to the off side off the front foot
nips back in from a length outside off stump and goes close to off, but he had already chosen to leave it
gets front foot out to drive wide of cover for a run
for once Watson strays down the pads from a fuller length, and he shuffles to tickle it fine enough to pick up four
settles back again to the outside off stump line and good length, he lets it go immediately
left alone outside off stump again, this one came back in a tad and kept low too
gets bat and pad close and drives this one away to point with an open face
whoa, walks two feet outside off stump but Watson shortens the length and follows him, and he pushes away to mid off
steered calmly down to third man from wide outside off
jabs at one that comes in with the angle from round the wicket, almost chops it on
nicely done, spirits out to the pitch of a length ball and drives it to cover
cramps him for room with one that cuts back in from short of a length, defended down the track
crack! full and some width outside off stump, he needs no more invitation, gets to the pitch and creams it past extra cover, no one moved
goes down the pads with the angle, and he picks a single through square leg
just about back of a length, he gets deep in the crease to push it on the off side
rides the bounce on this one outside off and looks to cut, but chops it in the ground, one leg in the air as he does that, full marks for intent
147.3 kph low full toss outside off stump, he throws the bat at it, and gets it fine to the third man boundary off a thick edge
squirts it out to point and scampers down for the run, before he is frantically sent back, and makes it back in time
stays on the back foot to a fuller delivery, has worked for Canada so far that style, and pats it away towards mid off
smoked off the front foot, but finds extra cover in the way
Johnson goes down the pads with that angle from round the stumps, and is picked away wide of fine leg, deep square leg runs to his right and just stops it from trickling in to the ropes
gets it outside off from just short of a length this time, left alone as it carries nicely to the keeper
thats the line from round the stumps that troubles the right hander, just short of a length around off stump and forcing him to push at it, he does so and gets beaten
and again, Johnson gets it spot on, and he ends up stabbing at it off the front foot, somehow it eludes the edge
a bit wider and fuller outside off stump, left alone this time
overdoes the angle on this one and gets it down the leg side
now he gets it to seam away from short of a length outside off stump, but wide enough for the batsman to shoulder arms
starts with a full toss low on the leg stump, pushed back down the ground
tossed up on middle and turning on leg, he goes down on the knee and sweeps forcefully to fine leg
gets some bounce now, and turn too, but down the leg side
more turn and bounce, this time on middle, he shuffles across and works it to fine leg
the line is awry from Krejza at the moment, another one turns down leg ans is nudged fine for a couple
better now, tossed up just outside off, he drives with the turn and midwicket dives to field
and again turns down the leg side, tickled fine for a single, not the start Krejza and Ponting would have wanted
Johnson gets this one to move away from a length outside off, left alone comfortably
surges forward and meets a length ball with a firm push that ends it to point
smashed off the front foot, a full one outside off and he drives it to the man at sweeper cover
slower one at 126.2 kph wide outside off, he picks it late and slaps it away to point
shuffles on off stump, gets front foot out and pushes this one to short extra cover

Johnson gets the edge for some fine stuff from round the stumps, but it falls short of Watson at slip, this one was bowled on off stump, much fuller, got him to drive,and moves away slightly to get the edge
turns a fuller one to midwicket
comes forward to push a turning one to midwicket again
paddles this one from outside off stump, looked to be a touch pre-meditated, but he gets it down to fine leg
Krejza goes down the pads again from round the stumps, worked easily to fine leg
goes for the big slog sweep over deep square leg, gets it off the pads fine on the leg side
skips down and drives it along the ground with the turn to long on
lunges out to push an incoming delivery with an open face to point
walks outside the line of a short of a length ball to work it away to fine leg, deftly done
gets him to hop on his toes to one that gets slightly big on him with the angle from round the stumps, defended in to the off side
and gets the surprise bouncer on target, lot of shoulder in that one, he takes his eyes off the ball and tries to fend it away, and somehow gets it fine on the leg side
left alone outside the off stump as it goes across him
lets another one angles across him from a length outside off
makes room outside leg stump, and cuts this one that turns it from off stump, wide of sweeper cover
floats it full and outside off stump, gets him to drive off the front foot, along the ground to sweeper cover
turns in from middle stump, and goes in the air fine on the leg side as he tries to work it away
pushed away on the off side for a single
backs away outside leg stump, looking to go towards point, almost yorks himself as this one is flighted full, Haddin takes it cleanly as almost grazes off stump
touch short outside off, and he goes on the back foot to cut it away
hurries on outside off from a length, he is late on the shot and takes it on the glove as it bounces as well
hangs back in the crease, and plays away from the body to push this one away
Watsone drags this one wide outside off, he has to reach out to stab it in the air past point, where Steve Smith goes leaping in the air to his right but cannot take it
much fuller and closer to off stump, dug out down the track
all timing this one, gets one full on middle and leg, gets front foot out and brings down the bat at an angle to send it purring to the wide long on boundary
very full outside off stump, he squeezes out the drive to mid off
bowls it full outside off and is eased down to long on
tossed up and turning in from outside off, he lunges out and defends
mix-up, but no harm done, the non-striker wanted the single and had run halfway down the pith before being sent back as midwicket converged on the ball
now the single is on, tapped in front of cover, and goes through with a loud 'yes'
gets him to drive against the turn with a tossed up one outside off, that is what offspinners were meant to do, he mistimes it to mid off
defended off the front foot to smother the turn on this flighted one
squirted away to point off the back foot
eases into a languid drive that goes in the air but falls miles short of deepish mid off
again he drives off the front foot, this time the thick edge goes in the air towards third man
goes for the pull to one that was not short enough, misses as it keeps a bit low, Haddin had the bails off, too soon it turned out, as the backfoot came off the ground a second later
forces out on the front foot and pings mid off with the drive off a fuller one
stabs this length ball away on the off side, wants the single which is not there as Watson and Haddin are nearby
tossed up and turns in, worked away through square leg
comes forward to try and turn this one away through midwicket, Krejza slows it down and he cannot get it past that man
skips out with initiative, and pushes this one to long on
reaches well forward with a high elbow and guides it to point
Krejza thrown the bat high and wide in the air, he takes it and smashes it off the front foot, beats a leaping Ponting at extra cover
played out with the turn to the left of midwicket who cuts off the single
and what a welcome, 142,7 kph fuller one, and just lifted over the bowler's head straight down the ground
and again he tries to do it, Tait tries to fire the yorker in from wide of the crease, he pushes it in the air down the ground
now he bowls the short one, gets big on the batsman who brings it down on the off side
fired wide down the leg side
shot! comes forward confidently and belts this full delivery, but cannot get it past mid off who gets quickly to his left
called a wide, Tait went very full outside off stump with that slingy action
gets the line alright now, defended off the back foot
plays out a very full one in to the leg side
tossed up slowly, turns in and he gets a leading edge as he stretches out to work it away on the leg side
bowls it a tad short and he goes back to cut it wide of sweeper cover
some more width outside off and slapped away to sweeper cover again
wants to work away for a run wide of midwicket, cannot get it past him
produces the leading edge again, he shuffled to turn one from way outside off, but the ball rolls away safely towards extra cover
walks across the stumps to work this one away through square leg, but cannot get the single again
it does not seem a joke at all, short and wide goes Tait, and is creamed off the back foot wide of sweeper cover

that will do, Tait finally has a wicket, another short and wide enough, Bagai went flailing at it, had to reach out for it, and got a thick edge which Haddin took easily, thrown it away really, he was looking in control
and is away, guiding one that is coming in with the angle, to third man
bangs it in short and outside off stump, he looks to have a go initially before letting it go past

Tait goes full and on the pads, strikes him in front and Australia go up in appeal, umpire Saheba says no, Haddin wants the review, replays show it clipping leg stump, onfield call stands, he survives
pushed away to covers off the back foot
pushed out to point off the front foot
shuffles across to flick a fuller one from off stump to short fine leg
skips down the track now, Krejza shortens the length, he jabs it away on the off side, and the non-striker wills him on for the run
goes for the sweep from outside off stump and gets it wide of fine leg
sharp bounce for Krejza from outside off stump, he dabs it away awkwardly in the air where slip would have been

Krejza gets reward for tossing the ball up, he went for the big one down the ground, but with the turn Krejza is getting, got it in the air for Lee to take a fine low catch running in from long on, mid off was in the circle, but the turn did Hansra in
Tait hits the pads again right after drinks, Australia go for the review once more as umpire Saheba is unmoved, but he got an inside edge that saved him
Tait decides to decimate the stumps with a searing yorker, but he jabs down his bat at it somehow, is flung in the air with the impact, comes down on all fours, but lives on

Tait bowls a fiery high full toss, at 146 kph, in search of the yorker, Surkari takes it on the inner right thigh, very close to the box,he is surprised, and right away goes down writhing in pain, Tait runs to him to apologise, he is now getting up on his feet
bowled 'em, 147.1 kph fuller one outside off stump, he had been stung by that blow the previous delivery and went for the ambitious cover drive, got an inside edge that clattered on to the stumps
almost gets through him with the yorker, he jams down the bat at it in the end
unfurls a lovely front foot drive this time to pick up the single to sweeper cover
bowls it full just outside off stump and he punches it to sweeper cover
has a swing at a full one on the stumps, and gets it off the inside edge wide of fine leg

Lee with the broadest of smiles, 115.1 kph, what a comedown in pace, super slower one, bang on middle stump, Cheema had no clue about it, doesn't help it the normal pace is around 145, plays all over it too early, and the ball takes out middle stump

how is that not out? just how? Lee strikes him on the front pad with a pacy and very full delivery, his bat was nowhere close to the ball, Billy says not out, the ball would have taken out middle and leg, Lee just ran down the track initially, he was so convinced he had his man
jams away another fuller one on the off side
Lee bowls one on a length this time, and he blocks it away
fires this one full and down the leg side
lets this one go, it came back in from a very full length, and contrived to miss the off stump
another full one on the stumps, there is no respite, jabbed away to extra cover
now Tait goes back of a length, super stuff, makes him hop on the toes to bring it down
still not off the mark, gets some width off this full delivery, but stabs it away in the air to point
bounces in from a length, but wide outside off stump, and left alone easily
digs it short of a good length, hurries in to the batsman who goes deep in the crease to defend
goes for the kill with a 146.3 kph full delivery on middle stump, this is lovely to watch, driven away to mid off

115.6 kph and full once more, he picks the slower one wide outside off stump, and goes forward to smash it past extra cover who gets a hand to it, it is Ponting, quite a run for the man at sweeper cover but he gets to it in the end
bounces awkwardly outside off stump, left alone
almost does a Tait, goes for the yorker and it ends up as a full toss, not as high as the one Tait bowled, and it is played away on the off side off the pads with an open face
on-the-money bouncer, takes off around off stump, but he sees it and sways away
goes across the right hander, who looks to push at it, but then pulls out of the shot
digs in the short one and pulls it wide down the leg side
now he gets it on target again, just outside off stump, this time he has a push at it, and is beaten
Johnson's turn to go full on the stumps, defended away to mid off
dropped Watson at wide slip, Johnson got one to cut away awkwardly past the batsman, who tried to steer it, but the edge flew to the left of Watson, who went low down but dropped it
there is no justice if you are a bowler, now he goes for a swing to a length ball outside off stump, and misses
patted back to the bowler, still not off the mark on debut
rides the bounce on this one outside off to steer it to third man
goes on the back foot and stabs away a wide one to sweeper cover
Lee targets the wickets with the full delivery, but he gets bat on ball to push it down the track
this one jags back in from short of a length, and he punches it away on the off side
slower one ends up as a loopy dipping full toss, patted away down the track
jabs away the yorker outside leg stump through midwicket
139.2 searing short delivery that takes off around off stump, he is beaten as he pushes at it
this is the other Johnson, slings one full and miles outside the off stump with a lot of shoulder, bounces after it passes the crease
reverts to the normal self, gets one on the stumps which is defended away

Nitish has had enough of all this searching examination from the quicks, he gets a fuller one and tries to lift it back over Johnson's head, but only gets it high in the air for mid off to settle under it
hangs the bat outside off stump to a length ball that goes in the air but falls short of mid off
Baidwan is away, uses the pace on this one on the pads to flick it past midwicket who gives up the chase as the outfield takes over
now he calmly leaves alone one outside off
turned to short fine leg off the back foot, the non-striker runs his half of the pitch twice, and gets back in time
more turn down the leg side, and worked backward of square
eased down the ground to long on
sharp turn from outside off, hits the pads but down the leg side
oops, fires this one in quick and wide outside off stump
slower and closer to off stump, pushed back to the bowler
gets it to turn in to the batsman from outside off who calmly pats it back
goes searching for a length ball angled outside off stump, and cannot find it, keeper collects
shortish one dug in to the body, shuffles and whips it down to fine leg
has a loose waft at one that is not far from off stump, but luck hasn't found Johnson on the right side today
good work from Mitch, gets out of that slingy action as the length ball is pushed back at him, and fires in the throw at the striker's end
squeezes out a full delivery towards point, but cannot get the single
that will fetch him four, waits on a fuller one to angle in to him, and slams it between bowler and mid off with a big followthrough
tucked away off the pads wide of midwicket
off the inside edge on to the leg side as he pushes out
slapped away to sweeper cover
steered to short third man from the crease
comes down the track but Krejza sees him and drags it shorter, can't do much with it
this time he gets a run as he charges down the track and stabs it away
tossed up generously as a low full toss that is patted back to Smith
takes a step out and drives a fuller on wide of mid on for a quick run
short and turning away, cut to point off the back foot
another short one, this time he gets the connection and placement right off the cut, to the right of sweeper cover
defended off the front foot back to the bowler
touch short again, width too, he gets it away to sweeper cover off the back foot

this is like the inside out tennis forehands that Federer unfurls, well this one is not unfurled it is slogged away, short and turning in from outside off, and he gets it over mid off even as he backs away outside leg stump

Krejza gets him this time, got him to charge down the track and have a big heave, the ball went miles in the air, enough for both Smith and Ponting to go for the catch, Ponting it is who takes it cleanly in the end, just brushes into Smith who was hanging around, and then bangs the ball in to the ground in anger
worked away off the hip as this one bounces om leg stump
tossed up and gets it to turn away from his forward push, Haddin whips off the bails but he is in
goes up for the lbw, but he managed to get an inside edge as he tried to turn it across the line
goes for the sweep on a knee and gets it to short fine leg
tossed up outside off stump, driven for a run, and Australia concede an overthrow
Canada bring up the 200 with a nudge of a single
takes this one on the full and eases it to long on
down the track and bashed down to long off
pushed through outside off stump, and he pats it towards covers
one more single to long off, Australia have allowed things to drift
rides the bounce on a wide one outside off to cut it away wide of point
and goes past the outside edge with one that angles in close to off stump
tries to steer from close to off stump, and is beaten again
merrily swings off the front foot, and still cannot connect outside off
slower one, draws him forward and gets him to push in the air, Ponting at short extra cover dives to his left, but it falls just short, might have taken it on that little finger
Lee gets one on the stumps, and shatters them, from round the wicket with that angle, Balaji looked to flick it, but played all around it,
pushed through around off stump and played down the track
cut away to sweeper cover off the back foot
tosses it up outside off, but he gets to the pitch and picks up a single to long off
Osinde tries to take off in the Bangalore evening, but the thick edge eludes short third man who runs to his right but cannot get there in time
worked away on the leg side off the front foot
goes with the turn this time, and gets four for it, gets toe the pitch of the ball and lifts it wide of sweeper cover
goes for the yorker on the stumps, stabbed off the inside edge backward of square leg

Osinde dug out the yorker, but forgot to run, realised he would have to when the non-striker was almost at his end, Clarke charged in from covers and fired in the throw to Ponting at the non-striker's, who took off the bails, but dropped the ball before that, as replays confirmed
gets big on him from short of a length, fended away on the leg side
145.5 kph high full toss gets Lee his fourth, Whatham backed away to the leg side, and looked to have a go at it, but it was too quick for him, and took out the stumps off the inside edge

inn2.comm: jaffa from Osinde! Lands one short of a length and gets it to jump away like a fiend, and Watson pulls the bat back inside the line.
Osinde is getting lift steep as the face of the Niagra falls. Watson lets another one go outside off. Bangalore evening, ball nipping around under lights? I must be imagining this.
this one also goes through nicely outside off, Watson stays on the crease and shoulders arms
he lands one closer to Watson, who leans into a check drive to wide mid off

and now he has Haddin fishing with a classic away swinger. Don't think any Ugandan has better seam position than that. Curls into a line outside off and then goes away even as Haddin is sucked into the drive. So close to the outside edge
that's one memorable over from Osinde who has got another ball to do a Garner on Haddin, landing back of a length and taking off. Haddin does well to weave away from the line.
length ball on off stump to start off, easier for Watson who gets across to cover the line and defend
ooh, this one nips in off the seam as Watson plays a half-hearted forward defensive. Inside edge squeezed away to the leg side.
too short and wide outside off, Haddin is away with a guided steer to third man
angles in from slightly wide and holds its line, as Watson defends from the crease

oh Cheema! He's dropped a swirler. Short of a length delivery, not quite there for the pull but Watson went through with the shot. The fact that he could not get entirely under it meant the top edge took off behind mid on. Cheema moved back and seemed to have enough time, but he did not judge it well as he back-pedalled.
hmm, edgy start this. Another inside edge to an inducker, squirts away to the leg side.
lovely delivery, fuller than his normal fare in the previous over and nips away off the seam. Haddin just about covers the line as he presses forward to defend
again, a bit of a legcutter, played off the outside half towards the off side
ah, Haddin gets a four, with some help from Nitish at point who moves slowly and dives over the ball. Haddin charges, makes room as he backs away and times the square drive really well
he charges out again, Osinder keeps it short and follows him, and Haddin plays a clumsy nothing shot that goes nowhere.
short again, targeting the body and Haddin is rushed into the pull shot. He bottom-edges it without timing to midwicket for a single
that away seam again. Lands on a length and goes away from Watson who wisely lets it go this time. Can Canada keep up the intensity?

I have seen Bollywood actors run faster than that, in slow motion shots. Cheema moves like a snail that's sleeping and gives Haddin another four. Haddin looks to force the pull away and doesn't time it at all. It looks like a single past mid on. Cheema keeps chasing and then dives, and can't pull it back.
another shortish ball, another ungainly pull from Haddin to a ball that's not there for the shot even as he charges out.
back of a length on off stump. Haddin covers the line and defends down the track
Australia are living on edge here. Literally. Baidwan offers a mile of width outside off and Haddin slashes hard over the slip and through to third man
better line, just outside the off and defended into the off side
slow legcutter drifts onto the pads and Haddin glances to short third man for a single
shortish ball outside off, Haddin rides the bounce properly and defends towards point
short and a touch too wide outside off, at 131 kph. Haddin stays back and steers into the covers. Not much carry or movement in this over.
that's more like it, Osinde lands it back of a length on off stump and gets it to go away. Haddin hurriedly gets the back foot across to defend to the off side
closer to the stumps, but Haddin stays put on the back foot to defend into the off side
top bowling from Osinde, he's bowling to the field. Haddin again forces the steer without timing towards point.

Haddin has luck now, squared up by another peachy legcutter from Osinde, he gets the outside edge straight to where second slip would have been. Alas, the second slip isn't there any more and it is down to third man for four
short of a length on off stump, Watson check drives to the off side
back of a length is how Baidwan's got 12 World Cup wickets and he sticks to the plan. Watson again plays calmly into the covers
straighter this time, bordering on middle and off as Watson covers the line to defend

the cheek from Watson. He's played the late cut to a seamer, despite not having any room, and knowing that first slip is not around any more. Expertly done, the upper flick of the wrists just as the ball came on, and another dismaying boundary through third man
straighter this time in compensation, Watson pushes to mid on for a single
Haddin defends the final delivery from the crease into the covers
over-pitched on off stump, Watto drives without timing to mid on

whoa, tight single and he just makes it. Watson dinks a short ball on the pads to mid on and takes off. Hiral runs in from midwicket and has the left-arm pick up and throw advantage. He misses though, as Watson hurries in.
this one keeps low, Haddin was stuck on the back foot and did well to bring the bat down at the last moment and defend to the leg side
Haddin's manufactured another boundary, not sure what he was trying to do as he moved his front foot away to the leg side, but he ended up carving it pretty well inside out over the covers.

another close shave, Haddin's sporting a smooth, red chin now. Short ball coming in from outside off, Haddin goes for a loose pull and under-edges it. The ball lands near off stump, evaluates its options and then chooses to bounce over the furniture and go away.
he ends the over by pushing a length ball into the off side. Canada need some luck here.
short of a length and angling into Watson who defends to the leg side from the crease

sublime timing from Watson, just plonks the front foot across and flows through the line. He probably was early on the shot, but he middled it really well. What looked like a check drive ended as a lofted boundary to long on
short of a length again on middle stump, worked around the pads to the leg side
fuller length to Haddin who plays an iffy, all-over-the-shop kind of stroke down the ground without moving the feet. He makes almost no contact
back of a length on off stump and punched confidently into the covers

if he did not edge that, Haddin might have escaped again. Inducker from back of a length, cramps him into another hoicked pull across the line. Umpire Saheba turns down the appeal, Baidwan wants a review. Bagai thinks long and hard, and chooses not to refer it. The ball came in and thudded into the pads in front of middle and off. Middle and leg were being hit and replays confirm that did not get an inside edge. Canada should have reviewed it!
Watto runs like the wind and gets two, glancing off the pads to deep backward square leg and charging back before the throw can be deflected onto the stumps by Bagai
back of a length on off stump, and defended to the off side

another huge appeal, this one seemed to be heading down the leg side. Boy, Bagai takes for ever to decide whether he should review it. This time, he does. It's a full delivery, swooping into the line of leg stump as Watson tries to work it to the leg side without much feet movement. Oh, replays say he's nicked it. A review wasted now. Canada are not playing this right.
good delivery, another inducking yorker squeezing into Watson's pads and he squeezes it down to backward square leg
heavy ball on middle and off, Haddin hops back to ride the bounce and defends to the leg side as it comes at 135 kph
shortens the length to end the over, Haddin feels from the crease and manages to defend to the off side.
dainty inducker, Watson covers the line and punches past the bowler. Haddin strays out of the crease but is wisely sent back in time.
fullish length on off stump, driven out to mid off. Another dot delivery.
angles into the pads, Watsom works the drive to mid on after coming across the stumps.
Watson is being kept on a right leash. Baidwan keeps landing them short of a length and Watson is looking to see away this opening burst
short, but not a half-tracker. Watson looks to pull and can't time it.
that's a maiden from Baidwan, Watson defends calmly to the off side
angles into the pads, Haddin flicks straight to midwcket without timing and they have another single
shortish ball on off stump, Haddin hops up to defend to the off side
Watson's not timing them at all. For once Osinde over-pitched on the stumps, and Watson inside edges the drive onto the pads and down the track.

ah, I take that back. Watson times one perfectly as a tiring Osinde sprays it on the pads. Not full enough for the flick, but Watson just gets the bat around with a delicate turn of the wrists and it runs away between mid on and midwicket
full and straight this time, Watson inside edges the on-drive to wide mid on
Osinde needs a break. Over-pitched outside leg, and Watson flicks to deep square leg for a single
ah, he drops the first one too short and Watson pulls fiercely to deep midwicket for one
another short ball, no dew in Bangalore, but he's yet to get a grip on the ball. Haddin pulls fine for a single
better length, lands this outside off and gets it to break away. Watson covers the line and defends
aha, the bait outside off, looped up generously and inviting the off-drive. Watson has a go and it goes past the edge
straighter ball, Watson covers the line and defends down the track

oho, Canada are letting the Australians get away here. Rao sends down the third half-tracker of the over, Watson sets himself up and pulls it high. Nitish at deep midwicket seemed to move slowly to his right. I think he didn't pick it at all. The ball went not more than two feet away from where he was.
Haddin steers a single to third man
offcutter comes in from back of a length, Watson is cramped for room as he tries to steer, and misses to make contact
fuller on off at a friendly pace, Watson on-drives to long on for a single
Haddin quietly dabs another single to third man as Cheema keeps it short of a length outside off
nips in off the seam again, Watson forces a defensive shot from the crease down the track
slower ball goes wrong, dawdles in at 112 kph, full and wide outside off. Watson just quietly drives into the covers for a single
Rao lands this on leg stump, and Watson turns it off the pads for a single
nice searching loopy delivery outside off, Haddin prods without getting across and gets it to the leg side off the inner edge
good line, lands on leg and breaks away. Haddin hangs back and defends down the track
too short, Haddin rocks back and cracks the cut in front of point for a single
boy, he's bowling quite a few half-trackers, but this one comes on fast to Watson before he can really pack a punch into the pull shot.
short again on leg stump, Haddin guides the pull to deep midwicket for one
short of a length and coming in with the angle, Haddin drives off the back foot to midwicket
shifts the line to outside off, Haddin leans into the check-drive and gets it to mid off
Haddin has another go, back of a length delivery coming into him and he under-edges the pull past leg stump. The Aussies want to stamp their authority but Canada are not letting them off.
fuller and straighter on off stump, Watson defends solidly into the off side
that's a Watson copyright. Not too short, coming in with the angle, Watson sets up a solid base and whacks the pull well in front of square. Natural, original and effective - the Watto pull.
ends the over by steering a single into the covers
Rao keeps it on the pads all the time, Watto works it off the back foot to square leg for one
turning away from middle and off, steered carefully into the covers off the back foot
strays onto the pads this time, Haddin nudges a single backward of square
over-pitched on the lag stump, worked to the leg side carefully
over-pitched on leg stump, played down the track
Rao's bowling too many poor balls here, this one is short and wide and turning away. Haddin cuts it away past point for a couple more.
tossed up and turning in, worked off the front foot to the leg side
short of a length on the pads, nudged away to the leg side for a single
Haddin leans out to drive a full ball outside off into the covers for a single
shortish ball, Watson is late on the pull and can't get it away for more than a single
Haddin covers the line of an offie turning in and works it to the leg side for one
Watson pushes another single down the ground. Australia are doing this in singles.
loopy but not too full on off, Watson defends down the track
leans out to a flighted ball, and defends to the offside off the outer half of the bat
sprays this down the leg side, Watto gets a single as he looks to flick. It goes fine off the pad.
tossed up on leg, Haddin stays back and defends
short ball, looks to cut and plays it without timing to the covers
Haddin retains strike with a steer to short third man for one more
Haddin eases a fullish ball to midwicket and thinks of one, but Watson isn't interested
speared in on middle and turning in, Haddin works it to square leg
breaks in from outside off, Watson leans out into a dour defensive shot
works this one with the turn to square leg
full on middle, Watson on-drives past mid on, but still can't get the single
Watson finally gets the single down the track
over-pitched on leg stump, driven down the ground for one

not really sure how that did not hit the stumps. Rao finally flights one on middle and leg and gets it to break away nicely. Haddin plays the ugliest of slog sweep, the kind that even Steve Waugh wouldn't appreciate, and he misses. The ball bounces a mile and hence misses the stumps. Haddin dragged the back foot out as he played that shot. Bagai doesn't gather cleanly and breaks the stumps without the ball in his gloves. Did the ball land on the stumps? Did the bails come off before the ball hit the stumps? Too much doubt. Haddin, somehow, survives.
huge lbw appeal now, Haddin squared up by sharp spin from middle and leg, and it hits in front of off. Not given and not reviewed.
tossed up on off stump, Haddin leans out to drive into the covers

nicely done Haddin. When he times the ball, there are few to beat him. Tossed up on middle and off, he leans out and dumps it clean and straight over mid on. The ball lands on the rope and comes back in. For the first time ever, I'm seeing a six being given the ball did not clear the ropes.
short this time, Haddin prances back and cuts into the covers for one
good length on off stump, punched straight to long on and Hansra is really slow to cover it, they get a couple
back of a length outside off, Watson gets forward and across to play it into the covers
hmm, nifty offcutter from Baidwan, Watson plays all over it and is struck in front of middle and leg. It was surely going further down.
straight ball outside off, Watson guides cautiously to third man for a single
Haddin moves to the leg side, Baidwan sees him and lands a slow offcutter outside off, forcing Haddin to steer carefully into the covers
Haddin chips out this time and nurdles fine off the pads to retain strike
back of a length outside off, some really lazy fielding at third man from Hansra allows Haddin a couple as he steers. Even a direct hit would have done the job.
full delivery on the stumps, punched solidly to mid on for a single
slower ball outside off, Watson dabs it backward of point and thinks of a single but the fielder covers ground quickly
Watson gets another single to third man, steering one from outside off safely
fifty to Haddin, he's had his chances and he's made use of them. Over-pitched ball from Osinde, coming in with the angle and Haddin lofts it over wide mid on with a clean swipe of the bat.

that's as delicate as they come. Inventive, innovative and industrious. Length ball on off stump, not the kind you steer, but that's just what Haddin does, opening the face and lofting it over the covers. Quite unusual, and well done.
length ball comes into Watson's pads and he clips it backward of square for a single
right, Haddin is going after the bowling here. Slow bouncer goes awry, sits up and asks to be hammered, he thumps it to deep backward square leg. Thankfully there's a fielder there.
Watson looks to nudge off the pads to the leg side but finds backward square leg
Watson has 50 now, digging out a full delivery outside off with a forced cover drive for one
back of a length on the pads, worked through midwicket  for one more

Watson's completely missed the slower ball, he plays the leg side swipe in the 2007 edition of the World Cup, the ball comes in present tense, four years later. It goes off something, down to third man for four. It's been that kind of evening for Canada.

boy, how many edges have we seen from Australia tonight? Cheema again slips in the off cutter, Haddin plays the cut and gets the inside egde, which finds a way between the stumps and the keeper. Four more to fine leg
Haddin backs away and tries to cut, but can't get it away past point
he's really looking for the boundary, this time he moves back and to the off side, lining Cheema up for the leg side heave, but can't get it past midwicket
this is pretty smart Powerplay batting. The field is in on the off side, Haddin waits for the slower ball to come along and then slaps it on the up over the covers.
Haddin's making merry while the lights shine. Cheema slides one onto the pads, and Haddin easily whips through backward square leg. Australia are charging to a win here.
full and on off stump, Haddin clips to square leg for a single
Haddin again tries to move away and drill a length ball down the ground. Single to long on
Watson gets one on the pads and hoicks it along to deep backward square leg for one
full delivery just outside off, Haddin make contact with the steer
full toss on leg stump, Haddin drives fluidly to mid off for one more
slower ball on off stump, Watson waits and clips to long on for a single
legcutter on off stump, Haddin hangs on the crease and dabs it square.
loopy on middle and off, breaking away and defended to the off side

Watson has hit that into MG Road. Almost. Rao lands this really short, Watson gets those biceps behind it and brutalises it over midwicket. Menacingly efficient. 94 metres it travels, and the crowd is reluctant to return the ball.
over-pitched on off stump, defended with the spin into the covers
Watson misses the slog sweep this time, full and a foot wide outside off, he swipes and misses
short and wide, Rao's been a letdown so far, Watson cuts fiercely to cover

oh boy, Watson is sure covering some real estate with his savage slog sweeps. This one is fuller, and his blast just keeps going, and going, and going. 99 metres by the time it decides to land over wide long on. Rao has been routed. Its the second biggest six of the World Cup after KOB against England.
Haddin does the wise thing, pushing a single down the ground and handing it to Watto.
Watto leans out to a flighted ball on off and dinks a single to cover.
Haddin chips out to the flight and pushes a single to mid on
speared into the pads, Watson nurdles to short fine leg
flat outside off, Watson stays content to defend from the crease

he's hitting them from both ends now. Davison does his bit by flighting gently on off stump, Watson reaches across to the pitch and just tees off smoothly. Ernie Els would have been proud of the shot. Lands a mile away in the stands at long on. That's the longest six of the tournament! 104 m. Usain Bolt would have taken over 9.72 seconds to get there. Watson did it slightly sooner.
back of a length on off stump, Haddin can't force the ball into the off side
now he pats into the covers for a single
ok, this is just pure violence. R rated stuff. These spinners don't stand a chance. Hiral meekly lands one on the leg stump and Watson smashes the leather off it as it sails over midwicket.
fuller from Patel, Watson can't quite get under it, so he just gets four instead of six, with a forced pull just over midwicket
Hiral Patel's day is ending the way it began. Unfortunately, he's on the other side now. Shorter ball, Watson waits and dumps it straight back down the ground.
bosh again, this is ending in a hurry. Watson reaches out to a loopy ball on the stumps and hits another straight four
Haddin knows his 100 is under threat, so he gets into the act. Full toss on off stump, he just eases it gracefully to midwicket for four
majestic from Haddin. Jumps out to the flight of Davison's offie and tees off down the ground for another six. They are just flying in all directions now.
Davison wisely spears down the leg side and Haddin nudges a single behind square
similar delivery to Watson, who flicks to the leg side for one more
ah, finally a wicket. Davison has struck in his last game with a flat ball landing on leg and turning further down. Haddin tickles it along into Bagai's gloves. He's missed a 100 here.
tossed up outside off, driven into the covers for one
after ages, a batsman beaten outside off. Back of a length ball outside off, Ponting struts into a forward defensive prod and misses
fuller on off, he still plays from the crease to third man for a single

Watson has missed his 100 too. This immense compulsion to hit sixes has finally cost him his wicket. He wanted to pull this. It wasn't straight enough. He still wanted to pull this. It wasn't short enough. He still wanted to pull this. Ends up trying to whack it over long on, but finds the man in the deep.
length ball on the stumps, punched straight to mid on
slow bouncer, Ponting pulls out of the pull shot late and it is through to Bagai
fuller ball on off stump, driven fluently straight to mid off.
short and wide outside off, Clarke is away with a sparkling cut in front of square. Take that, Osinde.
back of a length on middle and off, Clarke punches to mid on
Clarke drives wide of mid off, and thinks of a single but the fielder gets across quickly
short of a length outside off, and he lets it go through to the keeper

Canada aren't the best fielding side in this World Cup. Hansra the culprit again at mid on, as Clarke drives a length ball fluently down the ground. Hansra moves slowly and puts it a pointless dive as the ball chugs past
good bouncer outside off, Clarke drops his wrists in a hurry to let it go
short of a length on off stump, Ponting defends solidly to the off side
over-pitched on the stumps, Ponting gets a single with a drive to the left of mid on, who fields the ball this time
whoa, steep bouncer that, and Clarke does well to pull out of the pull shot as it flies past him to the keeper
short of a length outside off from Baidwan, Clarke defends down the track
short and sitting up just outside off, Clarke cuts well but straight to point
short of a length on middle and off, defended down the track and that will be drinks. If Watto and Haddin hadn't got out, this game would have ended by now.
back of a length outside off, Ponting hangs back and defends to the off side
short ball, comes on slowly at 128 kph and Ponting controls the pull to deep midwicket
length ball on off stump, Clarke cuts straight into the ground and into point's hands
short ball ends on the hips, Clarke works it to square leg for one
short again, Ponting quietly taps to the leg side for a single
too wide down the leg side and called
back of a length on off stump, solidly defended into the covers as Ponting and Clarke get what little batting practice they can.
loopy on the pads, Ponting deflects backward of square for one
over-pitched on off, Clarke drives into the covers for one more
looped up on middle and leg, Clarke defends off the front foot
top shot from Clarke, skips out like a beaver, gets to the pitch and drives it right back past Rao and all the way to the straight boundary.
too short and wide, Clarke cuts away with the spin through the covers for one more
Ponting gets a single as well, cutting a short ball into the covers
short of a length outside off, Ponting opens the face and defends to the off side

a bad day for Ponting comes to a forgettable end. Hide the TVs, is the joke doing the rounds. His bowlers struggled to bowl out Canada. Steve Smith nearly muffed a catch that was his. And now he's not got the batting practice he wanted. And he's again perished to the short ball. Late on the pull, pops it up to square leg meekly. A catch for Davison now, this is not as bad way to retire.
White gingerly pokes out to the off side
back of a length on off stump, played off the back foot into the off side
White levels the scores with a smooth backfoot cover drive. He waits on the back foot to a short of length ball and punches it cleanly through the cordon
Osinde denies White the pleasure of hitting the winning run by landing a bouncer in his own half. Bowden signals wide, and that's the end of Canada's World Cup campaign.
